 KYW; Frank Sylva\nno\u2019s, WIBO; the Syncopators, WGN;\ndinner dance, WCHI.\n7:3o\u2014Lix Rldey\u2019s, WIBO.\n7:4s\u2014Remington Welch\u2019s, WIBO.\nB\u2014Frank Sylvano\u2019s, WIBO; Avis Mac-\nDonald\u2019s, WJJD.\n9 \u2014George Devron\u2019s, WIBO.\n10:30 \u2014Johnny Hamp\u2019s, KYW; the Syn\ncopators, WGN.\n11\u2014Frank Sylvano\u2019s. WIBO; three-hour\ndance bill starts on WMAQ; Ted Flo\nrito\u2019s, WGN.\n11:02\u2014Phil Spitalny\u2019s, KYW.\nner\u2019s, WENR.\n11:45\u2014Frank Sylvano\u2019s, WIBO; Paul\nWhiteban\u2019s, WBBM.\n12\u2014Louis Panlco\u2019s, KYW; Lix Riley\u2019s,\nWIBO; Clyde McCoy\u2019s, WGN.\n12:15\u2014Johnny Hamp\u2019s, KYW; George\nDevron\u2019s, WIBO; Merry Garden,\nWBBM.\n12:30\u2014Remington Welch\u2019s, WIBO; Jan\nGarber\u2019s, WBBM; Sol Wagner\u2019s,\nWENR.\n12:45\u2014Louis Panlco\u2019s, KYW.\nI\u2014Frank Sylvano\u2019s, WIBO; Ben Ber\nnie\u2019s, WBBM.\nI:3o\u2014Jimmy Garrigan\u2019s, WIBO; Jan\nGarber\u2019s, WBBM.\nVARIETY.\ns\u2014Howard L. Peterson, organist, WJJD;\nMaillard\u2019s musicale, KYW.\nS:2O\u2014D. A. R. speaker, WBBM.\ns:3o\u2014Paul Zimm, violinist with orches\ntra, WCFL; concert orchestra, WJJD;\nHydrox program with Uncle Bob,\nKYW; organ concert, WBBM.\ns:4s\u2014Civic Shakespeare society, WMAQ\n6\u2014Variety bill, WCFL; dinner music,\nWENR; Curtiss contest, KYW.\n6:ls\u2014lrma Glen, organist, WJJD.\n6:3o\u2014Dinner concert, WJJD.\n6:4s\u2014Goshen musical program, KYW;\nHelen Morse, blues singer, WCHI.\n7\u2014Al Carney, organist, WCFL; musical\ncomedy revue, WJJD; eventtme melo\ndies, WLS; Larry and Duke. KYW.\n7:3o\u2014Main Street Crusader, WCHI.\n11:15\u2014Ben Bernie\u2019s, WBBM; Sol Wog-\n\u2014BY SWAN\nNORTH DAKOTA'S\nCAPITOL BORNS;\nHALLS ARE OSED\nBIS MARK, N. D.\u2014Departments\nof the North Dakota state govern\nment were taking up temporary\nquarters in halls, hotels, office and\npublic buildings today while offi\ncials rushed plans for erection of a\ncapitol to replace the historic struc\nture which burned Sunday. In the\nsmouldering ruins of the old capitol\nwere the ashes of documents and\nrecords which it had cost thousands\nof dollars to collect and many of\nwhich never can be replaced.\nStill Fighting Flames.\nFiremen still were pumping wa\nter onto the wreckage of what was\nconsidered the finest building in the\nwest at the time of its construction\nin 1884.\nThe fire, of unknown origin, left\nhomeless the state legislature,\nwhich is to convene Jan. 6.\nGov. George F. Shafer had\nplanned to recommend in his inaug\nural message that a new capitol be\nbuilt at once. He now will ask that\nan emergency appropriation bill be\nrushed in the coming session.\nWas Brick Structure.\nThe old capital was a four-story\nbrick building. The fire started on\nthe fourth floor.\nState officials joined with firemen\nin carrying records from the lower\nLET US\nSMILE\nODE TO OCR\nWISCONSIN\nWINTER\nHow can snow\nThrill us so.\n\u2014dear dear\u2014\nHIT BY TRAIN;\nISCRITICAL\nRufus Rarely, Jr., former in\nmate of the Barely mansion, well\nknown point of interest, declared\nm today that the\nsolution of the\nu n e Deployment\nproblem will\ncome the return\nof prosperity.\n\u201cThe trend is\nd e finitely up-\nI I I ward,\u201d he told\nU '1 newspaper men,\nML taking a trend\nroin\njZ/Tf S*; case and dis\nplaying it to\nthem.\n\u201cMy, but that\u2019s a brief case,\nisn\u2019t it?\u201d one of them showed in\ntelligence enough to remark.\n\u2014lousy\u2014\nThere are kids all over being told;\n\u2019\u2019Don\u2019t leave the chair so near the\nstove; it dries up the wood. They\u2019re\ngoing to grow up and get married and\ngo to jail and say \u201cYes, sir\u201d and'\nscrape egg-yellow off of plates. But\nright now someone is saying: \u201cDon\u2019t\nleave the chair so near the stove; it\ndries up the wood.\u201d Murderers and\ndopes and school teachers and gen\nerals, they say \u201cOh, yah,\u2019\u2019 and push\nthe chairs away.\n\u2014whats the use\u2014\nHorse-Scope\nu lt the stars incite\njb uj Abis\nTaurus is in Leo\u2019s pasture at\nthis time, and the seers warn\nwomen who are married to men\nwith firecracker tempers to re\nfrain from sharjiening lead pen\ncils with their hubby\u2019s pet razor.\nThe wise ones prophesy that\nduring the present configuration\nmatrimonial bureaus will be bait\ning their hooks with tricky ad\nvertisements. While this sway\ncontinues \u201cLonesome Lemanuels\u201d\nand \u201cHeartsick Harriets\u201d are ad\nvised to fill up their ink wells\nwith banana skins.\nChildren born on this day will\nbe so proud that, they will fall\nasleep ever night with a looking\nglass in their hand.\nEbenezer Onesima Pushbroom\nwas born on this day and will bo\nremembered as the only white\nwing that ever wore a full dress\nsuit.\n\u2014good luck dearie\u2014\nAiowPl\n7 ovicell;\nfa\nIP\nU E\nL, C.\" l JO l -\"\"2'.\nNo woman gets a square deal\nfrom a sewing circle.\n\u2014os os os-\nLAUGH DEPT.\nGladstone was an inspiration\nto younger men on rare occasions,\nand always was glad to give them\na helping word, hoping they\nwould pay for the drinks.\nOne of them once asked the\naged statesman, \u201cTo what, sir, do\nyou attribute your great sue.\ncess?\u201d\n\u201cTwo things,\u201d Gladstone re\nplied, cleaning out his pockets,\n\u201cHonesty and sagacity.\u201d\n\u201cAnd what is honesty, sir?\u201d\nasked the ambitious young bar.\nrister, for such he was.\n\u201cAlways keep your word once\nyou have given it,\u201d was Glad\nstone\u2019s lousy definition.\n\u201cAnd sagacity, pray what is\nthat?\u201d\n\u201cNever give it,\u201d was the witty\nreply given by Gladstone.\n\u2014dear dear\u2014\nI wonder where I\ncan get some Easter\neggs. J. A. J.\nBERLIN A new issue of cur.\nrency notes is being prepared by\nthe state printing works. The new\nnotes, which will be even more dif\nficult to counterfeit than the old,\nwill have their first issue in 1931.\nLONDON\u2014 A woman with 26\nnames, all but on of which are\nChristian names, was given power\nof attorney in a will filed here to\nday.\nLONDON Sturdy constables\nhere are to be the judges of when\na Christmas carol ceases to be\nmusic and becomes a penny-jerker.\nfloors, but only a comparatively few\nwere saved.\nInsurance on the building and\ncontents totaled $600,000. The loss\nwas estimated as being considera\nbi\u00a3 myre than that amount.\nPage Eight","height":"28998","width":"21618"}}
